"The word you want," said our Person, "is cong–òre, feminine gender, I learned it from my mother."

"Then it's sugrob in Russian," said Armande and added dryly: "Only there won't be much snow there in August."

Julia laughed. Julia looked happy and healthy. Julia had grown even prettier than she had been two years ago. Shall I now see her in dreams with those new eyebrows, that new long hair? How fast do dreams catch up with new fas